#### **WEBHOOK ENDPOINTS**

##### `POST /webhooks/github`

GitHub webhook handler (automatickÃ© deployment).

**GitHub Webhook Settings:**
- Payload URL: `http://your-domain.com/api/webhooks/github`
- Content type: `application/json`
- Events: Push, Release
- Secret: VygenerovanÃ© heslo

**Request Body (od GitHubu):**
```json
{
  "event": "push",
  "ref": "refs/heads/main",
  "repository": {
    "full_name": "user/app-repo",
    "clone_url": "https://github.com/user/app-repo.git"
  },
  "pusher": {
    "name": "John Doe"
  },
  "commits": [
    {
      "id": "abc123def456",
      "message": "Fix: memory leak",
      "author": {
        "name": "John Doe",
        "email": "john@example.com"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Response 200:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Webhook received, deployment initiated",
  "data": {
    "webhookId": "uuid",
    "deploymentId": "uuid",
    "appId": "uuid",
    "status": "queued",
    "message": "Deployment job queued"
  }
}
```

